reviews.text:
We bought two pastrami sandwiches on rye.  The meat was tender and delicious.  I've lived in the area over 30 years and always heard they were good but never tried them.   My mistake!  The sandwich was better than Katz's and a hell of a lot cheaper.  Next I try the pastrami.   I went back on Feb 24,2021 and got two more pastrami sandwiches as well as shrimp salad and Swedish meatballs.  The server was excellent as I did give him (indecision grief)  which he took very well and kept his calm around me which is usually impossible.   I tipped him two bucks.  The  bill ran over 35 bucks but it's cheaper than the delicatessen I went to  a few weeks ago.  The food is made fresh and all looks delicious.  I'm too big anyway and there's never enough time for all the food.
Revisited 11/4/25 for two pastrami sandwiches.   It took longer than usual and my wife and were looking forward to it.  The sandwiches came out an i said to the server if i knew it was going to take so long i would've added french fries as well.  The bill came to $ 28.00 and i went home.  We opened only one sandwich which unfortunately was tasty but tough!  Disappointing, It'll be a long time before i go back.  Service,courtesy and store is clean and well stocked.
Great food
We LOVE Manor deli!!!

Manor Delicatessen is a classic for a reason. Grabbed breakfast here this morning and had their pastrami on rye with a root beer. The pastrami was perfectly tender and flavorful, and the rye bread was fresh. It's a simple, classic deli sandwich done right. A great local spot for a satisfying meal.
This was friat time here, since I lost my mo., I whould take her all the time, and it did not disappoint,  I took my son and he loved it.. I have to stop in more often..

Food is a solid 8 out of 10. I tried a varietyÂ of things, especially the things others recommended. Not blow you out of the water good, but pretty darn good. The star of the show here was the carrot cake, which nobody has mentioned. It's probably the best carrot cake I've ever had in my life. I don't understand why this isn't viral carrot cake, like they should be famous for it.
They clearly respect the store and the customers, the place is spotless clean and organized so good a military sergeantÂ would approve.
They are very friendly to everyone coming in. These guys are pros and know service. I will be coming back to try more because they have some good stuff here and it's worth trying out whatever else they have.
Mystic deli
The best deli in woodhaven queens

Good Morning!

Delicious fresh food daily
Rueben was alright, quite greasy, corned beef was decent
Food was good and the place is very neat and well kept

This store is amazingly clean & well preserved. It looks like you walked into a deli from 1969. Its spotless. Its deli case is filled with all types of delicious food. I got a pastrami on rye w/ fries. Its pretty good pastrami. In my opinion its not made on site. Its a pastrami brisket ordered from a provisions company & maybe steamed in the back. It just does not have that fall apart real kosher deli pastrami texture. That being said its very flavorful sandwitch. I definetly enjoyed it. I give the pastrami a 7/10

Layout/atmosphere
*German deli; hot/cold food; takeout only

Food/drink
*Reuben (with corned beef) on rye - Good; tender beef; melted Swiss; little messy but bread didnâ€™t completely fall apart from its contents
*Macaroni salad - Good
*Cucumber salad - Good

Amazing deli.  This deli has been in Woodhaven for many years and I could see why.  The service is good and so are the prices.  The place is big and very clean.  They have regular deli staples and they also have prepared dishes.  I got the stuffed Chicken Breast and it was ðŸ˜‹.  I also got the Coleslaw which was too shredded for my taste but in terms of taste it was good.  If I'm back in the neighborhood I will go back to try some of their other prepared food.

Everything here is delicious
Customer service is at its best.
Excellent food.
Always very clean

Omg.. you open the door expecting a normal deli n then you get hit with this fragrance, this perfume of bratwurst, cabbage rolls n whatever else theyre blessing us with that day n you never want to leave! Simply delicious pastrami and everything else! Came back for business from south Carolina n brought people with me just for them to explore since they liked German food. As usual, they did not disappoint! A must visit!
I recently visited Manor Deli. The best brat I've had in years.

Everybody in the neighborhood knows this place. If you don't, you should; and you do now.

Manor Deli has been here for over 100 years.  It's the place to go for excellent deli food in Woodhaven.

Its roots are German and this deli are a cut above - way above -  the norm.

In fact they should be standard for which others strive.

The quality of their food is high but their prices are not.

So drop in and get a sandwich, or sliced deli meets, or a salad from their cold bar, or something hot from the hot bar.....

There's lots to choose from.

It's all good - in fact it's great
Classic neighborhood spot itâ€™s lasted so long for a reason
Sandwiches are good, but a little pricey. Also parking is difficult sometimes.
That's the place to go , it's the best .
Everything we got delivered was excellent and very fresh. Nice old time deli feel
Amazing
Old school New York Deli
Great authentic deli.

I've been to Manor deli several times over the years. Every time they are consistent with their high quality food and service. The deli is always clean and well organized, the staff easy to deal with, and most importantly the food isâ€¦
Best swedish meatballs E.V.A.
Great old school delicatessen.   Hot and cold food. Some great deli classic sandwiches.

Years ago when I worked for State Farm on Jamaica Avenue, we used to order from Manor all the time
Then in 2006 my boss retired and I moved on to State Farm in Jamaica Queens and was too far away
My family were trying to decide to cater Christmas , I suggested Manor .
We ordered Swedish Meatballs, Pasta with Chicken and Broccoli, Eggplant Rollatini, Chicken Tenders with Honey Mistard and a tray of mini sandwiches which had Ham, Turkey, Roastbeef and cheeses
The whole dinner was delicious and Awesome
Everything tasted great and was cooked just right
Thank You Manor for making our Christmas wonderful
We will definately be ordering again !!

Catered food for New Year's Day! Everything was delicious and well worth the money! Ordered a tray of finger sandwiches ( Manor calls them finger sandwiches) other deli's pass off as a regular size. Ordered a full tray of chicken tenders,â€¦

I am not writing this review to tell you what to do with your hard-earned money. I am going to share my thoughts and you make your own decision if you would like to try this place or not. I have been wanting to try out this place for someâ€¦
Really... As good as it gets. Had the corned beef, pastrami, a hot dog, the Woodhaven Manor special hero.  The only thing missing was a Dr. Brown's black cherry soda.

Clean, clean, super clean. Did I mention itâ€™s clean?
Best deli in NYC. Itâ€™s been there forever, and no wonder. This is how delis used to be. This is how they SHOULD be.
The best deli in queens  hey all of  nyc.  I use them for all my catering needs.  The best

The sandwiches here are great. I've had some of the hot dinners too like the chicken meatloaf and chicken parm which were tasty. I really like their burgers and chicken sandwiches. Their corned beef sandwich is great, unlike some delis inâ€¦
Love the food just wish they open later so I could pick up food for dinner

I Grew up in the neighborhood my whole life, I called there for delivery for the first time, I was craving for pastrami on rye and a knish and omg it was the best I ever had from that classic deli, ya gained ya self a new customer, Ty

I've been going here for over 35 years and it's still Great!! It is one of my favorite Deli's. I told my wife on the way home, it's like going back it time. I love the Macaroni and Potato  salad. The meats are so fresh and tender and veryâ€¦
The stuffed chicken breast is amazing. Juicy chicken stuffed with broccoli and cheese. All the sides look delicious but I stick with the mashed potatoes every time.
Great Fresh food , and run by great people! I cant recommend this place enough. If it's just for a great sandwich or great plates of hot food!

Great neighborhood deli with all the varieties you'd hope for and then some. Fresh, delicious foods prepared daily and served by some of the nicest people around. And, let's not forget how clean and organized the place is. A true gem worth repeated visits as there are new dishes to try out every time you're there.

I saw this deli while passing through Jamaica Ave and seemed like a legit deli to try out. Ordered the pastrami sandwich on rye and mustard. My expectation was the pastrami would be house made but it was tasted like regular packaged one.â€¦

There goes my rent money! It's pricey,  or I would probably eat here 3x daily! I just moved here,  & must learn to control myself or I'll be fat and homeless quick! Food is amazing, & excellent customer service when they remember to put utensils in your carry out, or delivery bag.

Best deli in Woodhaven, top 3 in Queens, top 10 in the whole city. Timeless. Excellent sandwiches and the daily specials of hot food are enough for 2 meals.  I moved and the saddest part was saying goodbye to this place.

It's one of the last original german deli that's been around since the 1970's when I was a child in Woodhaven. They make authentic, heroes, sandwiches, cold salads & other plates & dishes which are always freshly made. Another plus is theyâ€¦

My family, friends and I have have been coming to manor deli for years. I've now moved out of the area but still make a point to come back simply because the quality of the food and service are consistently excellent. I have also come to them to cater a few special events and was very happy. I highly recommend  giving them a try.

Love this landmark; my late grandmother always brought us deli food from here when we were kids. I still come here for their heroes and potatoe salad. Also the decor is nostalgic of what used to be good IMO.

Honestly the best bacon egg and cheese I've had in a while. Its actually hard to find places that serve regular bacon nowadays and finding it here was awesome. Staff super polite. So next time you go for a baconeggandcheese ask what type of bacon your using ðŸ˜‰â€¦
The only other time I had pastrami this good was from Katz Deli. Everything there is delicious and fresh. Fast service with nice friendly workers. It will definitely be my go to stop from now on.
Great German deli. They have the best potato salad in the USA. Large portions of hot foods. Specials every day. Great huge sandwiches. Homemade soups. YUUUUMMMMMY>Cheap

I ordered some apple turnovers paid for them by accident they sold them when I went to pick them up but then they personally delivered them the next day and gave me more then I ordered  they r truly honorable staff of people n have the best tasting food around. Thank you again for great customer service!
One of the best deli's I ever visited! Never got tired of buying my sandwich and meals for the last 25 years. The management, cleanness and service is the best!
Manor Delicatessen is part of Woodhaven's history.  This business provides first class service and outstanding food for about 100 years since they started serving the community.â€¦
This Deli's food is amazing. My favorite is the blt's as they make them with the freshest ingredients. This deli is also very clean and the customer service is great.
Great old fashioned German deli food. Last of its kind around most of Queens. Try the cucumber salad and their food dishes. Don't leave without a meatcake!!!
You just can't find dell's like this anymore.  Food is amazing.  Place is clean as a whistle. Prices are a little higher than average, but you pay for very high quality here.

Found a cockroach in my coffee.....you wait 30 minutes in line just for them to mess up your order and give you attitude about it..They are more focused on joking around with each other than making your food right. Never again.
